Function argument validation and property validation might involve type and/or size coercion, which might affect the run-time performance of the generated code.

The type and/or size of these arguments as specified in the output arguments validation block differs from the type/size that the code generator deduced from the body of the function. This mismatch might cause an extraneous data copy in the generated code.

The type and/or size of these properties as specified using property validation differs from the type/size of the values assigned to the class properties. This mismatch might cause an extraneous data copy in the generated code.
Insights on handling automatic parallelization of for-loops.
Array or variable access pattern inside the loop is not suitable for parallel execution.
Enable 'OptimizeReductions' option in the config to automatically parallelize loops with reduction operations.
Loops with reduction operations are not supported for automatic parallelization.

Saturating integer arithmetic prevents automatic parallelization of this loop. If appropriate for your application, disable the code configuration parameter Saturate On Integer Overflow ('SaturateOnIntegerOverflow') to allow the code generator to automatically parallelize this loop.
This for-loop contains bitwise reduction operations on noninteger types. The code generator automatically parallelizes such loops only if the bitwise operations use integer types.
Loops that contain parallel loops are not supported for automatic parallelization.
Loops that access persistent variables are not supported for automatic parallelization.
While loops are not supported for automatic parallelization.
To automatically parallelize for-loop, the loop variable must be consecutive increasing integer.

The code generator did not automatically parallelize this for-loop because it has too few loop iterations relative to the number of available threads.

The code generator generates both sequential and parallel versions of the for-loops. At run time, depending on the number of loop iterations, the version of the generated loop that runs faster is executed.
Set 'EnableOpenMP' to true to generate code with parallelized for-loops.
